The paper discusses user voting behavior on three different websites, which involves aspects of social media, human-computer interaction, information retrieval, and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
